Root cause: A step in the iFlow parses the message body as JSON using a strict GSON JsonReader, but the runtime payload is not valid JSON (empty or non‑JSON such as text/HTML). The parser fails at the first character (line 1, column 1), triggering an internal server error.
Suggested fix: Parsing a non‑JSON payload as JSON. Add a guard before the JSON parsing step: route based on Content-Type and/or a payload startsWith('{','[') check, and only invoke the JSON to XML/JSON parser when the payload is valid JSON. Alternatively enforce/normalize upstream to always return valid JSON. If an HTTP call precedes parsing, validate the response Content-Type and handle non‑JSON responses via a separate branch or error handler.
